div.p:
And whereas no provision is made in the above mentioned treaty nor in any
                            subsequent agreement for the payment of light and harbor dues in the
                            dominions of His Highness the Sultan;

Now, therefore, the High Contracting Parties have to that end resolved to conclude a convention, and have for this purpose appointed their plenipotentiaries, to wit:
The President of the United States of America, John Hay, Secretary of State of the United States; and
His Britannic Majesty The Right Honorable Sir Michael H. Herbert, G.C.M.Gr., C.B., His Majesty’s Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary;
